-- Arabtec Sees No Need to Increase Provisions After $81.4 Million Last Year
-- B y   S h a j i   M a t h e w
-- 2010-10-19T04:06:11Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-19/arabtec-sees-no-need-to-increase-provisions-after-81-4-million-last-year.html
Arabtec Holding Co. said there is no
need for the company to increase provisions this year after the
biggest builder in the United Arab Emirates by market value
booked provisions worth 299 million dirhams at the end of last
year.  The company was commenting on media reports citing its
chief financial officer, according to an Arabtec statement on
Dubai bourse today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
